The lack of intelligent thought is scary. Whoever referred to Obama as a Muslim, stop drinking or smoking whatever it is that's fogging your brain cells. Then go seek mental help, because you greatly need it. SMH! Yes, both parties share part of the blame. No, nobody is perfect. Yes immigration is an issue, but it has been an issue for YEARS. And we are a land of immigrants. A path to citizenship is the logical, moral and cost effective thing to do. I'm not entirely sure what the best way to do that is, but people need to come to the table to have a rational discussion about it. It is ridiculous to think we could simply deport the HUGE number of immigrants who have made America home. The cost would be immense, and it would cause many more issues beyond those people's lives. You are not being realistic. Implement a path to citizenship and then make better policies for moving forward. Why are some of you so hateful? Do you really think illegal immigrants are what's hurting your lives? I feel sorry for you. Have a little compassion. All these people want is to be a contributing member of society and have a better life.

And why would that be? You do realize that the Republican and Democratic parties have been taken over by multi-national corporations, the academic Elite, and even governmental bodies that want Global governance. Donald Trump is an outsider and the establishment will do everything in their power, Republican and Democrat, to take him down because he goes against the grain. He speaks his mind and he won't be put into the establishments little box. Hillary Clinton has scandals going back to the 1980s. She's been involved in insider trading, there's a lot of people that have known her that have come up dead under mysterious circumstances, she perjured herself in front of Congress, she lied about the emails she's stole the primary election from Bernie Sanders and you want this person as our president? The person that says when she landed in Kosovo she was under sniper fire and then they played the tape and nothing of the sort happened? I've been on both sides of the aisle I grew up Republican I quickly changed to Democrat after Bush's Wars the National Defense authorization Act the Patriot Act and other unconstitutional legislation. I worked on Obama's campaign in 2008 for three months. I believed everything he said, 90% of it or more turned out to be a lie so I started digging a little deeper. Multinational corporations, Elite people in government have a revolving door system and they have captured our Republic. Although Donald Trump is not perfect by any means he's the best chance that we have at getting America back on track. If we vote in Hillary things will stay the same. Actually they will keep getting worse just like under Obama, and she will continue Obama's Legacy of destroying the Constitution just like George Bush. It's time to stop with the partisan politics and attacks and get to the truth of the matter that this country has been hijacked by multi-national corporations and we are heading towards a One World Government. In other words, a total tyranny worldwide.
